# Collectibles_Design

## 1. Applies when
There are collectibles, a codex, relics, fragments, sequence collectibles, or
relationship-triggering items.

## 2. This document owns
Collectible classification; narrative relics; codex entries; relationship-trigger
fragments; sequence collectibles; collection feedback.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Ordinary resources; inventory; trading; material economy (all Resource_And_Economy).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. Classification (Pure / Relational / Sequence) ·
3. Pure background collectibles · 4. Relational collectibles ·
5. Sequence collectibles · 6. Codex & cross-playthrough · 7. Boundaries · 8. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- Collectibles vs Resource — narrative objects vs economy resources.
- Collectibles vs Mission — a relational item triggers a request (owned by Mission).
- Collectibles vs Narrative Bible — a relic references truth, does not own it.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Resource-like items must not appear here (COLLECTIBLES-NO-RESOURCE check).
- A collectible may have narrative feedback but no numeric reward.
